menu "breadboard: bb_event"

config BB_EVENT_MAX_TOPICS
    int "Maximum number of event topics"
    default 8
    range 1 256
    help
        Maximum number of topics that can be created at runtime.
        Default 8 covers typical usage (update.available, mining.share.*,
        ota.progress, etc.) and saves ~2 KB BSS vs the old default of 16.
        Raise if your application attaches more than 8 concurrent topics.

config BB_EVENT_QUEUE_DEPTH
    int "Event queue depth per subscription"
    default 16
    range 1 256
    help
        Number of events that can be queued per subscription before
        the oldest event is dropped.

config BB_EVENT_MAX_PAYLOAD
    int "Maximum event payload size (bytes)"
    default 1024 if SPIRAM
    default 512
    range 0 4096
    help
        Maximum size of event payload data. Set to 0 if events
        contain only metadata.

        PSRAM-axis DERIVE (TA-517): default 1024 on SPIRAM boards, 512 on
        no-PSRAM boards, sized to carry a full telemetry-scale serialized
        payload without truncation.

endmenu
